"I know that all the other clubs who were hoping to be selected are  greatly disappointed. I wanted Novo Sancti Petri, but life sometimes is not so  sweet. We do not always get what we want.
"Everyone must forget any hard feelings and work altogether in assisting  Mr Patino, Valderrama and the Ryder Cup committee to show the world that Spain  is worthy of hosting this magnificent golf event."
Ballesteros resigned from the Ryder Cup committee earlier this month  because he felt key discussions were taking place behind his back.
